{
  "slug": "security-guidance",
  "name": "Security Guidance",
  "type": "plugin",
  "description": "Security review for Claude-generated code. Pattern-based warnings on edits, LLM-powered diff review on Stop, and an agentic commit reviewer that catches injection, XSS, SSRF, hardcoded secrets, and 25+ other vulnerability classes.",
  "longDescription": "Three layers of security review for Claude-generated code:\n\n- **Pattern warnings**: fast regex checks on every edit via hooks\n- **LLM diff review**: reviews the full diff on Stop using the Claude Agent SDK\n- **Agentic commit reviewer**: deep review at commit time\n\nCatches injection, XSS, SSRF, hardcoded secrets, and **25+ vulnerability classes** overall. Implemented as Python hooks (`hooks/hooks.json`), no external service required.",
